Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle
over the @Smoked Paprika{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden,
~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve and peel the @Red Onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams} and pop them onto a piece of
#foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel.

Pop the @Garlic Cloves{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of foil with a
drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Pop the onion wedges onto one side of a medium #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the
middle shelf until tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

When the onion has been roasting for ~{5%minutes}, pop the tomato and
garlic parcels onto the tray alongside the onion.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Roast for the remaining time until softened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat (no oil). When hot,
add the @Diced Chorizo{120%grams} and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams},
@Mixed Herbs{1%sachet} and @Sugar{1%tsp}. Bring to the boil, then simmer
until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir through the @Butter{20%grams} until melted, then remove from the heat.

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{},
squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the garlic and @Mayonnaise{64%grams}.
Loosen with a splash of @water{} until you get a nice drizzling consistency.

When everything's ready, reheat the tomato sauce if needed.

Share the potato chunks, onion wedges and tomatoes between your ~bowls{}.

Spoon over the tomato and chorizo sauce. Drizzle over the garlic aioli.

Top with the @Wild Rocket{20%grams} to finish. Enjoy!